&lt;p>asda&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>CSS Variables Reminder</title><link>https://kirillbobyrev.com/notes/css-variables/</link><pubDate>Thu, 22 Feb 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://kirillbobyrev.com/notes/css-variables/</guid><description>&lt;p>CSS variables are defined with two dashes:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;">&lt;code class="language-css" data-lang="css">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">:&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#0550ae">root&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#1f2328">{&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#953800">--primary-color&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">:&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#0550ae">#3182ce&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">}&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>And used with the var() function:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;">&lt;code class="language-css" data-lang="css">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">.&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">button&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#1f2328">{&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#cf222e">background-color&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">:&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#6639ba">var&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">(&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#0550ae">--&lt;/span>primary&lt;span style="color:#0550ae">-&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#cf222e">color&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">);&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#1f2328">}&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>This enables easy theming and maintenance!&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Mobile Development Tips</title><link>https://kirillbobyrev.com/notes/mobile-development/</link><pubDate>Thu, 15 Feb 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://kirillbobyrev.com/notes/mobile-development/</guid><description>&lt;p>When developing for mobile, always test on real devices. Simulators can miss many real-world issues related to performance, touch sensitivity, and network behavior.&lt;/p>
