â€“ Dieter Rams&lt;/p>&lt;/blockquote></description></item><item><title>Git Branching Strategy</title><link>https://kirillbobyrev.com/notes/git-branching/</link><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://kirillbobyrev.com/notes/git-branching/</guid><description>&lt;p>For new projects, consider a simplified Git workflow:&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>&lt;code>main&lt;/code> - Production code&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;code>develop&lt;/code> - Integration branch&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Feature branches - Named with &lt;code>feature/name-of-feature&lt;/code>&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;p>This keeps things clean while still providing isolation for new features.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>